modules.description: Provides functions to connect to, write to, and read from Redis servers using Hiredis. Works with strings, lists, and hash maps as native OCaml types. Enables real-time data caching and session management in web applications.

Converts OCaml values to and from Hiredis RESP types, including strings, integers, arrays, errors, and status messages. Supports extraction of primitive types, arrays, and hash tables from RESP values with explicit error handling. Enables direct manipulation of Redis protocol data in OCaml applications.
